      <p class="desc">
        Takht Sri Patna Sahib, also known as **Harmandir Sahib, Patna**, is one of the five holiest Takhts (thrones) in Sikhism. 
        Located in **Patna, Bihar**, it marks the birthplace of **Guru Gobind Singh Ji**, the 10th Sikh Guru, born in 1666.
      </p>
      <p class="desc">
        This grand gurudwara was built by **Maharaja Ranjit Singh** in the 18th century. It houses ancient relics of Guru Gobind Singh Ji, including his weapons and sacred scriptures.
      </p>
      <p class="desc">
        Patna Sahib is a spiritual and architectural marvel that attracts lakhs of pilgrims and tourists from around the world. 
        The peaceful kirtan, langar (community kitchen), and holy sarovar (pond) add to the divinity of this sacred space.
      </p>

